name: parking of text #1
description:
Eyesight opens two fields of view: which sees all objects at the same time, and gaze that selects certain objects in the categories of shape, color, motion and type. Or between overall forms and singular forms. Sourced from the concept of "gestalt" from Max Wertheimer. Eye work is like parking attendants arranging vehicles that stop for incoming and outgoing ones. Parking of text a shadow for a break from the language.

by: afrizal malna
